<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading">Wordle tips and tricks</h2>



<p>To solve Wordle=E2=80=99s mystery word in as few tries as possible, you =
should lock in as many green and yellow tiles as possible early on. We=E2=
=80=99ve compiled a <a href=3D"https://wordraiders.com/guides/best-wordle-s=
tarting-words/">list of the best starting Words for Wordle</a>, which you c=
an use to open the game and increase your chances of winning.</p>



<p>The concept of Wordle is simple, but becoming a master at the game requi=
res a balance of ability and luck. By using the following advanced techniqu=
es, you too can increase your chances of completing each puzzle using a red=
uced number of turns:</p>



<ul class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li>Start strong: Choosing the best starting word is a must to reveal yello=
w and green tiles and significantly increase your chance of solving each pu=
zzle in fewer turns. On the contrary, choosing a poor starting word can res=
ult in only gray tiles, which only allow you to see which letters you shoul=
dn=E2=80=99t use again.</li>



<li>Locate vowels: Many players feel that an important strategy is to find =
vowels early on. To do this, try using vowel-heavy terms towards the start =
of the game. Finding vowels should significantly improve the accuracy of yo=
ur following turns.</li>



<li>Improve your vocabulary: Sometimes it=E2=80=99s hard to come up with th=
e next guess. The more words you know, the easier it is to find the right o=
ne. We advise you to read through and memorize some <a href=3D"https://word=
raiders.com/wordlists/5-letter-words/">5-letter words</a>, and you won=E2=
=80=99t get stuck coming up with the next guess.</li>



<li>Take your time: Wordle puzzles are released daily, so players have the =
duration of the day to find the solution. Due to this, players can take the=
ir time over each turn and come up with their best answers under little pre=
ssure.</li>



<li>Don=E2=80=99t repeat grays: Gray tiles indicate that the letter has bee=
n attempted and found to be not present in the puzzle solution. Using gray =
tiles in future turns will waste tile space that could instead be used on o=
ther letters that can give you more information.</li>



<li>Repeat letters with caution: Even if a tile turns yellow or green, the =
same letter may still be present more than once. Try to limit attempts that=
 use the same letter multiple times unless you are very confident they are =
successful.</li>



<li>Use US English: Wordle puzzles use an American English dictionary, so p=
layers who are used to British English should remember that certain words a=
re spelled differently, which can affect their word length.</li>



<li>Practice makes perfect: As with anything, playing the game regularly wi=
ll increase your chances of success. Even though Wordle is a daily game, le=
vels can be played multiple times. Through repetition, players can identify=
 areas to improve in their game.</li>



<li>Make sure that the word you=E2=80=99re about to guess next hasn=E2=80=
=99t already been a <a href=3D"https://wordraiders.com/solvers/past-wordle-=
answers/">Wordle solution in the past</a>.</li>
</ul>
